We first calculate the Quick Ratio by using the formula:

  Quick Ratio = (Current Assets – Inventory) / Current Liabilities

Using the ending amounts from the balance sheet:
  Current Assets = 20,314,894.50  
  Inventory = 9,100,000.00  
  Current Liabilities = 1,015,922.54

Thus,
  Quick Assets = 20,314,894.50 – 9,100,000.00 = 11,214,894.50  
  Quick Ratio = 11,214,894.50 / 1,015,922.54 ≈ 11.04

Next, the Net Profit Margin is calculated using:

  Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

From the income statement:
  Net Profit = 1,842,166.21  
  Total Revenue = 20,318,450.67

Thus,
  Net Profit Margin = (1,842,166.21 / 20,318,450.67) × 100% ≈ 9.07%

The final solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "11.04",
    "Net Profit Margin": "9.07%"
  }
}
